Description: Rim fragment of a large open pottery vessel; traces of a handle root on neck; wide ledge rim black glazed on inside, outside and top. Hard, red/brown clay, Munsell 2.5YR 7/4 (light reddish brown).
Curator's comments: The rim is comparable to the Typhon Situa (Schlotzhauer & Weber TD 238).
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 347)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
